---
layout: recipe
title: "Sikil P'ak"
description: "A smoky, fresh pepita and tomatillo sauce perfect for vegetables, tacos, and bowls."
notes: ""
prep_time: ""
cook_time: ""
rest_time: ""
total_time: "30m"
servings: "3 cups"
tags: 
  - sauce-dip
source_name: ""
source_url: ""
ingredients:
  - "¾ cup pepitas"
  - "4 tomatillos"
  - "2 shallots"
  - "2 teaspoons garlic"
  - "1 jalapeno"
  - "2 cups cilantro"
  - "2 teaspoons lime zest"
  - "¼ cup lime juice"
  - "1 teaspoon salt"
ingredients_subhead: ""
ingredients_2:
  - ""
preparations:
  - ""
directions:
  - "Toast the pepitas in a medium skillet over medium-high heat, stirring often, until lightly browned (5&nbsp;minutes)."
  - "Transfer the pepitas to a food processor and process until finely ground (30&nbsp;seconds)."
  - "In the same skillet, add the tomatillos, shallots, garlic, and jalapeño. Cook until charred on all sides (5&nbsp;minutes)."
  - "Add the cilantro, lime zest, lime juice, and salt to the food processor. Pulse about 20 times."
  - "Add the charred vegetables and process until chopped."
pairing: "Pairs well with vegetables, tortilla chips, crudités, tacos, bowls."
photos: []
---
